There was a good reason this guy was only second to bin Laden on the FBI's Most Wanted list: they're both killers of innocents. I can't see this level of screen presence in most of the new actors like Chris Pratt or even Christian Bale at times. Maybe Johnny is too well-known, too notorious for his own good. It's like Arnold at the height of his career. He was a joke to everyone, even though he had created some of the most legendary characters (Terminator) and spoke some of the greatest lines in film history. The same shit is happening to Tom Cruise. You're not seeing the actual acting. You're seeing what you want to see.
